parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine suddenly stops running
the vehicle loses power
the engine makes a knocking or grinding noise
the oil light comes on
the engine smells like burning oil
the vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rod bearing can cause the engine to seize or fail, leading to a loss of power and control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud knocking or grinding noise
the oil light comes on
the engine smells like burning oil
the vehicle loses power or stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, which can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The oil light comes on
the engine smells like burning oil
the vehicle uses excessive amounts of oil
the engine makes a loud knocking or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the knock sensor can cause the engine to fail or seize, leading to a loss of power and control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud knocking or grinding noise
the oil light comes on
the engine smells like burning oil
the vehicle loses power or stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering coupler can cause the steering wheel to make a clicking or clunking noise, leading to loss of power steering and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Clicking or clunking noise when turning the steering wheel
loose or uncontrollable steering wheel
vibration when hitting bumps or turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brake lights to stay on, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake lights stay on
inability to shift gears
vehicle skids or locks up when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Frequent oil changes needed
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Difficulty turning the steering wheel
power steering warning light on
vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Traction control warning light on
vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to ABS Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop
or the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect for Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in obtaining the necessary parts for the recall repair can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The contact receives notification of the recall but is unable to obtain the necessary parts for the repair
the contact is unable to schedule a repair appointment
or the contact is told that the parts are not available.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fire Risk due to Brake Fluid Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leak of brake fluid can cause a fire, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The contact notices a fuel or chemical odor
the vehicle catches fire
or the brake fluid is leaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Various Reasons
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop
or the vehicle is involved in an accident.
